column210: Notes applications are useful for shopping lists because they offer simple, easy-to-use, and convenient features that help you easily manage shopping tasks.
column211: If the shopping list is very long, using the Notes application can become somewhat confusing because all the items are displayed on the same page. In addition, some Notes applications may lack advanced features, such as reminders or automatic sorting, which can make the shopping experience less efficient or convenient
column212:
Sync feature: Allows users to sync their shopping list across multiple devices so they can view or edit the list at any time, anywhere.
Category: Add category labels to shopping lists, such as food, cosmetics, electronics, etc., to make it easier for users to organize and find the items they need.
Voice recognition: Allowing users to add items to shopping lists using voice commands will make it more convenient and fast.

column311:
Out of stock: It can be frustrating when the product you need is out of stock. This is especially frustrating if you've been walking around the store for a long time and can't find what you need.
Poor organizing: Grocery stores can be frustrating if they don't adequately organize and clean their shelves. Cluttered shelves and cluttered displays can make shopping difficult and unpleasant.
